This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses fairness metrics and regularization methods, which are common topics in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes biases in language models, which could potentially fall under the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes methods for improving fairness metrics without sacrificing perplexity and semantic similarity, which could be relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
